1.) The Multilevel Feedback Queue does follow the proper sequence for process enqueuing and dequeuing. However, there are times when the program 
gets stuck and will not finish. Other times, it will finish to completion. I believe that race conditions may cause this issue, although I am
not sure. 

Also, statistics (such as # of times a process was put in the queue, or # of times a process was blocked) were not included in this submission.

2.) To run the project, type "./oss" followed by any combination of these arguments (all of which are optional):
    a.) -h
    b.) -f [string for a logfile basename]

    Example: ./oss -f file.txt

3.) git information can be found in the '.git' folder inside this project submission. 
